# ClickAwayListener

IDS ClickAwayListener is used to monitor when the element loses focus because of a click-away.
This component is used in IDS Dropdown, DropdownButton, and SplitButton if you would like to see good examples of its usage.

## Installation & Import

```bash
yarn add @ids-ts/click-away-listener
```

```tsx
import { ClickAwayListener } from '@ids-ts/click-away-listener';
```

## Props API

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `children` | `(ref: (c?: HTMLElement \| null) => void) => ReactNode` | Yes | Function that receives a ref callback and returns a React node. |
| `onClickAway` | `(event: React.MouseEvent | React.KeyboardEvent)...` | No | * Callback on click away. |
| `useOnClick` | `boolean` | No | * Boolean prop to determine whether to use onClick event instead of onMouseUp. |

<details>
<summary>Full TypeScript Interface</summary>

```typescript
export interface ClickAwayListenerProps
  extends Omit<React.HTMLAttributes<any>, 'children'> {
  /**
   * Children prop, it should be a function to return a React node.
   */
  children: (
    ref: (c?: HTMLElement | null) => void | React.RefObject<HTMLElement>,
    props?: any
  ) => JSX.IntrinsicElements | React.ReactNode;
  /**
   * Callback on click away.
   */
  onClickAway?: (event: React.MouseEvent | React.KeyboardEvent) => void;
  /**
   * Boolean prop to determine whether to use onClick event instead of onMouseUp.
   */
  useOnClick?: boolean;
}
```

</details>

